   Interdisciplinary Programs

   The HRSA Bureau of Health Professions Division of Interdisciplinary
   Community-Based Programs focuses health professions education and
   training on identifying and meeting the health care needs of
   underserved communities. Programs assist academic health institutions
   with broad interdisciplinary expertise to form partnerships with states
   and communities to educate health professions students in
   community-based settings and also meet urgent health care needs.

   Programs
     * Area Health Education Centers
     * Geriatric Education Centers
     * Geriatric Training for Faculty in Medicine, Dentistry and
       Behavioral/Mental Health
     * Geriatric Academic Career Awards
     * Quentin N. Burdick Rural Program for Interdisciplinary Training
     * Health Education Training Centers
     * Allied Health Projects
     * Chiropractic Demonstration Projects

   Initiatives
     * Association for Medical Education and Research in Substance Abuse
       (not a federal site)
     * Ethnogeriatrics (not a federal site) developing a culturally and
       racially sensitive core curriculum on caring for a diverse aging
       population
     * Border Health: caring for underserved people living along the
       U.S.-Mexico border

   Collaborative Efforts
     * Primary Care Policy Fellowship de-mystifying federal policymaking
       for health care providers who care for underserved people.
       Co-sponsors: Department of Veterans Affairs and, from the U.S.
       Department of Health and Human Services, Agency for Healthcare
       Research and Quality, Health Care Financing Administration, Indian
       Health Service, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, and
       Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration.
     * HHS Secretary's Awards for Innovations in Health Promotion and
       Disease Prevention competition among health professions students
     * National Advisory Group for Interdisciplinary Community-Based
       Programs

